Dargah Shaji Baba us also situated in the campus this a naqshbandi silsila. Here is a graveyard also named Nau Mahla Graveyard which is used for only the Sadaat to burry in.
In this Masjid up to 15 aug 2010 the prayer was led by Hazrat Allama Mufti Qazi Abdul Rahim Bastavi he was longest period Imam in the masjid he started to led prayers in Mar 1961 and he was continually leading prayer up to the his last day of his his life which was 15 aug 2010

Here one Hauz is also for the people to ablution with fresh and clear water

featured_reviews.review_id:
Qila, Jama Masjid
Bareilly

This is very old masjid in Bareilly.
This place is located in Thana qila area.
Qila cloth market and sabzi mandi in north, Thana qila and Bara bazar in east, Mohalla zakhira, kanghi tola, in south and Qila railway crossing, Tilak inter college & Qila over bridge in west.

There are various restaurant nearby famous for delicious non veg food.
Qila market is also nearby, where we may get grains, pulses, clothes, hosiery items, utensils, grocery stationary & daily use items at wholesale price.

The masjid is very large and can accommodate a large number of gathering to offer namaz.
A large hauz (water pool) is also inside the masjid campus where peoples perform wuzu (ablution) before offering namaz.

A number of shops and residential rooms are also constructed along the outer walls of masjid to be given on rent to generate some income for masjid development.

The namaz is prayed in leadership of Mufti Khursheed alam sahab, who is nayab imam of jama masjid and shahar qazi of bareilly.
He is very talented, well educated in islamic studies and very gentle in nature.
